WEBVTT

00:01.401 --> 00:02.870
♪♪

00:02.870 --> 00:05.239
Well, this all looks good
to me.

00:05.239 --> 00:06.874
We're excited to get started
on the work.

00:06.874 --> 00:07.941
But before we do,

00:07.941 --> 00:09.276
just a couple of
quick questions.

00:09.276 --> 00:10.878
Lena,
I think you've covered

00:10.878 --> 00:12.145
everything
that matters,

00:12.145 --> 00:13.814
as well as a whole bunch
of other things

00:13.814 --> 00:15.649
that don't matter.

00:15.649 --> 00:16.650
We're all set.

00:16.650 --> 00:17.784
You're all set.

00:17.784 --> 00:20.420
I'm not all set.

00:20.420 --> 00:22.289
I'd like to get
a better picture of the man

00:22.289 --> 00:24.591
we'll be exposing
our children to.

00:24.591 --> 00:27.094
I will not expose myself
to children.

00:27.094 --> 00:29.162
How would you characterize
your relationship

00:29.162 --> 00:30.998
with Yelp reviewer
Maureen G.,

00:30.998 --> 00:33.033
who wrote,
"The work was strong,

00:33.033 --> 00:35.569
but not as strong
as the whiff of misogyny

00:35.569 --> 00:37.037
Vlad brought
into my home."

00:37.037 --> 00:38.238
End quote.

00:38.238 --> 00:40.173
Maureen G.
I remember.

00:40.173 --> 00:41.375
Like most women,

00:41.375 --> 00:43.677
she had nice legs
and bad ideas.

00:43.677 --> 00:45.913
You think most women
have nice legs?

00:45.913 --> 00:48.549
That's your problem
with what he said?

00:48.549 --> 00:49.549
I mean...

00:49.549 --> 00:50.450
Misogyny!

00:50.450 --> 00:51.818
And more than a whiff.

00:51.818 --> 00:54.621
Look, if you want the best,
you hire Vlad.

00:54.621 --> 00:56.857
So maybe I tell you
you look nice

00:56.857 --> 00:58.225
a couple of times.

00:59.092 --> 01:00.560
Maybe I don't.

01:00.560 --> 01:03.130
I'm not a glasses guy, anyway,
just so you know.

01:03.130 --> 01:05.832
Enjoy
your sideways house.

01:09.069 --> 01:10.704
I know
what you're doing.

01:10.704 --> 01:12.639
And I'm not gonna let you
sabotage the sale of this house

01:12.639 --> 01:15.342
by undermining every contractor
who tries to work on it.

01:15.342 --> 01:17.344
This is happening,
Lena.

01:17.344 --> 01:20.213
And it's my week,
so please leave.

01:20.213 --> 01:22.015
This is a common space.

01:22.015 --> 01:24.184
You have no power here.

01:24.184 --> 01:26.353
Be gone.

01:28.689 --> 01:30.090
Did you just Glinda me?

01:30.090 --> 01:31.992
♪♪

01:31.992 --> 01:35.495
♪ Keep giving me hope
for a better day ♪

01:35.495 --> 01:38.665
♪ Keep giving me love
to find a way ♪

01:38.665 --> 01:41.935
♪ Through this heaviness
I feel ♪

01:41.935 --> 01:48.375
♪ I just need someone to say
everything's okay ♪

01:48.375 --> 01:50.444
♪ Everything's okay ♪

01:50.444 --> 01:51.445
-- Captions by VITAC --

01:51.445 --> 01:52.746
[ Knocking on door ]

01:52.746 --> 01:53.847
Hey, Martin?

01:53.847 --> 01:55.716
Door's locked.

01:55.716 --> 01:57.017
My keys are inside.

01:57.017 --> 01:58.885
Okay.

01:58.885 --> 02:00.287
Thanks
for letting me know.

02:00.287 --> 02:02.155
Martin, open the door.

02:02.155 --> 02:04.858
It's not your week.

02:04.858 --> 02:06.126
Okay.

02:06.126 --> 02:07.260
You wanna go there?

02:07.260 --> 02:08.395
Do you want to go there?

02:08.395 --> 02:09.997
Oh, I'm already here.

02:09.997 --> 02:11.131
I see.

02:11.131 --> 02:12.432
Yeah,
you want to get nuts.

02:12.432 --> 02:14.334
Alright, let's get nuts.
Let's go --

02:14.334 --> 02:17.104
Wait, is that lunch
for our children?

02:17.104 --> 02:18.338
Yup.

02:18.338 --> 02:20.474
That is not nutritious.
Oh, well!

02:20.474 --> 02:22.142
Guess the kids
are having a cheat day.

02:22.142 --> 02:23.910
A cheat day?
A cheat day, yeah.

02:23.910 --> 02:24.878
You've got to be kidding.

02:24.878 --> 02:26.046
That is not a cheat day.

02:26.046 --> 02:27.681
That is
brown-bag diabetes.

02:27.681 --> 02:31.118
I no longer strive to reach your
unreachable standards, okay?

02:31.118 --> 02:32.486
And just like Vlad --

02:32.486 --> 02:34.888
the award-winning contractor
that you drove away --

02:34.888 --> 02:36.023
I don't work
for you.

02:36.023 --> 02:37.290
Big news, guys!

02:37.290 --> 02:38.558
[ Knocking on door ]

02:38.558 --> 02:39.860
♪♪

02:39.860 --> 02:41.662
Why is Mom locked out?

02:41.662 --> 02:43.397
Is she?

02:43.397 --> 02:46.833
Oh, Lena.
Why didn't you knock?

02:46.833 --> 02:50.337
Oh, look at that poor thing
out there.

02:52.706 --> 02:53.807
[ Lock clicks ]

02:53.807 --> 02:56.376
Aww, thank you,
sweetheart.

02:56.376 --> 02:59.946
So, what's your big news?

02:59.946 --> 03:01.114
I lost a tooth!

03:01.114 --> 03:03.316
[ Gasps ] Oh, my gosh.

03:03.316 --> 03:04.785
Well, wait till you try
your dad's lunch.

03:04.785 --> 03:06.119
You're gonna lose
all your teeth.

03:06.653 --> 03:08.922
Can I show this to Ajay
after school?

03:08.922 --> 03:10.457
I'm so sorry, sweetie.

03:10.457 --> 03:12.592
Ajay gets out of school
really late.

03:12.592 --> 03:15.128
But, um, what about
this weekend?

03:15.128 --> 03:16.463
I never get to see Ajay

03:16.463 --> 03:18.732
since he got into
that stupid school

03:18.732 --> 03:20.067
for smart kids.

03:20.067 --> 03:21.134
I know,

03:21.134 --> 03:22.469
but you'll always be
best friends

03:22.469 --> 03:23.937
no matter what.

03:23.937 --> 03:25.505
Or not.

03:26.740 --> 03:29.476
Hey, you may find
that you grow apart,

03:29.476 --> 03:31.878
get older,
develop different interests.

03:31.878 --> 03:33.313
Ajay goes his way to MIT.

03:33.313 --> 03:34.748
You go your way
to Chico State.

03:34.748 --> 03:36.349
Chico State?!
Martin: Mm-hmm.

03:36.349 --> 03:38.351
And then one day,

03:38.351 --> 03:41.021
you run into each other
on the street

03:41.021 --> 03:42.989
and you won't even remember
each other's names.

03:43.924 --> 03:45.692
Goodness gracious!

03:45.692 --> 03:47.160
Silly Daddy.

03:47.160 --> 03:49.362
Don't listen
to dumb silly Daddy.

03:49.362 --> 03:50.764
"Dumb silly Daddy"
is the only one

03:50.764 --> 03:52.699
who's gonna give it to you
straight around here, kid.

03:52.699 --> 03:54.901
So unless you want a load
of sunshine blown up your --

03:54.901 --> 03:57.404
Milo, why don't you go put
that chomper under your pillow

03:57.404 --> 03:58.805
so the Tooth Fairy
can find it.

03:58.805 --> 03:59.706
Okay!

03:59.706 --> 04:01.374
I wonder how much
she'll leave me!

04:01.374 --> 04:02.909
Not a penny, son.

04:04.711 --> 04:05.846
Not a penny.

04:07.314 --> 04:08.949
Because the Tooth Fairy...

04:10.150 --> 04:11.351
...isn't...

04:12.385 --> 04:13.653
...real.

04:14.421 --> 04:16.123
You shut
your dirty mouth!

04:16.123 --> 04:17.257
She's a lie, bro.

04:17.257 --> 04:20.527
Fairies don't exist.

04:20.527 --> 04:21.962
But money does.

04:23.797 --> 04:24.998
Huh?

04:24.998 --> 04:26.733
[ Chuckles ]
Whoa.

04:26.733 --> 04:27.934
Yeah.

04:27.934 --> 04:29.002
Cash, cash, cash!

04:29.002 --> 04:30.971
Cash, cash, cash!
Cash, cash, cash!

04:30.971 --> 04:32.405
Cash, cash!
Yeah.

04:32.405 --> 04:34.341
What in
the innocence-destroying hell

04:34.341 --> 04:35.575
are you doing?

04:35.575 --> 04:38.979
I'm done sheltering our kids
from reality,

04:38.979 --> 04:42.749
trying to be the perfect
phony baloney parent.

04:42.749 --> 04:45.185
On my weeks, I am going back
to parenting the way I want to.

04:45.185 --> 04:46.853
To punish me?

04:46.853 --> 04:48.088
♪♪

04:48.088 --> 04:49.689
[ Sighs ]

04:49.689 --> 04:52.192
[ Camera shutter clicks ]
Why?

04:52.192 --> 04:54.294
I'm Snapchatting Hazel.

04:54.294 --> 04:56.263
"All these apples,

04:56.263 --> 04:58.565
and you still
didn't pick me."

04:58.565 --> 04:59.966
Normally
I'd make fun of him,

04:59.966 --> 05:02.702
but his peers will take care
of that for me.

05:03.837 --> 05:05.572
What's the end game here,
bud?

05:05.572 --> 05:07.107
To make Hazel
feel sorry for me

05:07.107 --> 05:08.508
so she'll take me back.

05:08.508 --> 05:09.709
That won't work.

05:09.709 --> 05:10.877
She's not taking you back.

05:10.877 --> 05:12.312
Well, you know,
who knows?

05:12.312 --> 05:13.613
Maybe down the road,
the two of you --

05:13.613 --> 05:14.915
That's not helpful.

05:14.915 --> 05:15.882
Yes, it is!

05:15.882 --> 05:17.317
Down the road,
we'll what, Mom?

05:17.317 --> 05:18.351
Well, you could --

05:18.351 --> 05:19.486
Hey, hey, hey.

05:19.486 --> 05:20.754
It's not your week.

05:20.754 --> 05:21.888
[ Whistles ]

05:22.789 --> 05:23.790
[ Whistles ]

05:29.563 --> 05:31.531
[ Sighs ] Okay.

05:31.531 --> 05:34.968
Look Mace, you don't want Hazel
to pity you...

05:34.968 --> 05:36.069
Yes, I do.

05:36.069 --> 05:37.470
No, you don't, okay?

05:37.470 --> 05:39.573
You want her to miss
spending time with you.

05:39.573 --> 05:40.840
How do I do that?

05:40.840 --> 05:43.043
By living your best life, man,
you know?

05:43.043 --> 05:46.012
Like,
having a great time.

05:46.012 --> 05:48.782
And then rubbing her face in it
on social media!

05:50.050 --> 05:52.419
What's the most fun thing
you can think of?

05:53.353 --> 05:55.355
Kan Jam?
What?

05:55.355 --> 05:56.957
That lawn game
that we used to play,

05:56.957 --> 05:58.625
that Mom banned?

05:58.625 --> 05:59.960
She banned it?

05:59.960 --> 06:01.661
She said it was like
"putting two trash cans

06:01.661 --> 06:03.430
on the front lawn."

06:03.430 --> 06:05.699
In her defense,
that is what it is.

06:05.699 --> 06:08.969
Something Mom hates,
huh?

06:08.969 --> 06:10.837
That does sound fun.

06:10.837 --> 06:12.239
♪♪

06:12.239 --> 06:13.807
Let's go, man.

06:14.808 --> 06:15.942
Oh, that was close.
That was close.

06:15.942 --> 06:17.110
-What was that?
-That was close.

06:17.110 --> 06:18.211
Come on,
you got this.

06:18.211 --> 06:19.179
Mason: Hey, Mom.

06:19.179 --> 06:20.347
Dad reinstated Kan Jam.

06:20.347 --> 06:21.648
Did he, now?

06:21.648 --> 06:23.917
I know you said
it's a waste of time.

06:23.917 --> 06:26.519
No, I said it was
a waste basket.

06:26.519 --> 06:27.921
And another waste basket.

06:27.921 --> 06:29.522
That's literally
what it is.

06:29.522 --> 06:30.824
Hey, Ms. W.

06:30.824 --> 06:32.525
Hey.

06:32.525 --> 06:34.527
Heard you, uh,
weren't a big fan of the Kan.

06:34.527 --> 06:36.263
Truth be told, Jules,
I'm not.

06:36.263 --> 06:37.564
We're all having fun.

06:37.564 --> 06:39.032
I hope that's okay
with you?

06:39.032 --> 06:40.033
Are you kidding?!

06:40.033 --> 06:41.935
You know me.
I never want the fun to end.

06:41.935 --> 06:44.437
I do know you, and I never
would have characterized --

06:44.437 --> 06:47.774
Oh, Lena, what are you doing?!
We're in a drought!
[ All yelling ]

06:47.774 --> 06:49.042
Call my mom!
Turn it off!

06:49.042 --> 06:51.678
Anyway, I got him
with the sprinkler --

06:51.678 --> 06:54.014
but it wasn't gratifying
because it was a warm day,

06:54.014 --> 06:56.283
so I think it actually
cooled him off.

06:56.283 --> 06:59.286
You can never let him
get the upper hand. Ever.

06:59.286 --> 07:02.555
That's why I always give Arthur
the smaller piece of meat,

07:02.555 --> 07:04.124
even if I'm not hungry.

07:04.124 --> 07:06.159
And then if I can't finish,
I throw it in the garbage.

07:07.294 --> 07:09.529
Can I get you a glass of milk
to wash that down?

07:09.529 --> 07:12.032
Hey! Don't call them
"free samples"

07:12.032 --> 07:14.701
if they're gonna be laced
with your judgment.

07:14.701 --> 07:17.203
It no longer qualifies
as a free "sample," Maya,

07:17.203 --> 07:18.905
if all the little muffin chunks
that you ate

07:18.905 --> 07:20.507
add up
to a whole muffin.

07:20.507 --> 07:22.142
Um, I'm pregnant,

07:22.142 --> 07:25.111
and I have cravings
for free stuff.

07:25.111 --> 07:26.313
I'm telling you,

07:26.313 --> 07:29.049
Martin is intentionally
trying to upset me.

07:29.049 --> 07:30.750
I've never seen him
so vengeful.

07:30.750 --> 07:32.719
Well,
you contractor-blocked him.

07:32.719 --> 07:34.087
Yeah,
if it's really over,

07:34.087 --> 07:36.022
maybe just let him
fix up the house, you know,

07:36.022 --> 07:37.757
and then sell it
and move on.

07:37.757 --> 07:39.426
Oh, don't be naive.

07:39.426 --> 07:41.127
Martin doesn't want
to move on.

07:41.127 --> 07:42.662
He wants a war.

07:42.662 --> 07:44.164
[ Dog panting ]

07:44.164 --> 07:45.265
♪♪

07:45.265 --> 07:49.102
And I'm about to stockpile
my arsenal.

07:49.102 --> 07:51.338
Are you a good boy?

07:51.338 --> 07:53.707
Oh, you are.

07:53.707 --> 07:55.942
You are, aren't you?

07:55.942 --> 07:58.478
Is she about to weaponize
that dog?

07:58.478 --> 08:00.680
Martin
is super allergic.

08:00.680 --> 08:02.615
We don't know that.

08:02.615 --> 08:06.553
He claims he is,
but it's never been tested.

08:06.553 --> 08:10.056
That is some deeply sinister
[bleep] right there.

08:10.056 --> 08:12.025
♪♪

08:12.025 --> 08:14.894
Lena: Martin?

08:14.894 --> 08:17.230
Hey, Martin?

08:17.230 --> 08:18.498
Oh.

08:18.498 --> 08:20.166
You did laundry.

08:20.166 --> 08:22.102
That's very sweet.

08:22.102 --> 08:23.370
Now I feel bad.

08:23.370 --> 08:25.638
Oh, I'm sorry.

08:25.638 --> 08:27.240
Was this dry-clean only?

08:28.341 --> 08:29.509
Cashmere!

08:29.509 --> 08:30.710
My cashmere!

08:30.710 --> 08:31.911
Yeah. Yeah.

08:31.911 --> 08:33.213
I know how much
you love this thing,

08:33.213 --> 08:35.782
but unfortunately
I mishandled it,

08:35.782 --> 08:37.183
and now it's ruined.

08:37.183 --> 08:38.551
♪♪

08:38.551 --> 08:40.086
It's okay.

08:40.086 --> 08:40.787
It's cute.

08:40.787 --> 08:42.389
It's cute?
Mm-hmm.

08:42.389 --> 08:43.757
Think you can
still wear it?

08:43.757 --> 08:45.392
Oh, yeah.
Even though
it's doll-sized?

08:45.392 --> 08:46.526
Won't be too small?

08:46.526 --> 08:48.261
Nopey dopey.

08:48.261 --> 08:50.063
Okay. Fun phrase.

08:50.063 --> 08:50.964
Yeah.

08:50.964 --> 08:52.465
You know what else
is fun?

08:52.465 --> 08:53.666
Hmm?
[ Whistles ]

08:53.666 --> 08:55.201
[ Dog barks ]

08:55.201 --> 08:59.139
♪♪

08:59.139 --> 09:00.106
His name's Dander.

09:00.106 --> 09:02.542
Oh.
His name is Dander.

09:02.542 --> 09:04.010
His name is Dander?!

09:04.010 --> 09:04.811
Dander.

09:04.811 --> 09:06.546
I love you, Dander.

09:06.546 --> 09:08.748
Wait, isn't Dad allergic
to Dander?

09:08.748 --> 09:09.983
Who cares?

09:09.983 --> 09:11.718
What should be call him
for short?

09:11.718 --> 09:13.253
Dander!

09:13.253 --> 09:17.757
♪♪

09:17.757 --> 09:20.093
You did this,
Dander.

09:20.093 --> 09:21.428
♪♪

09:21.428 --> 09:23.663
You caused this pain.

09:26.032 --> 09:27.367
Sociopath.

09:27.367 --> 09:29.269
You're a sociopath.

09:29.269 --> 09:30.370
[ Door opens ]

09:30.370 --> 09:32.172
♪♪

09:32.172 --> 09:33.273
New look?

09:33.273 --> 09:36.543
Oh, you fool.

09:36.543 --> 09:38.144
What have you done?

09:38.144 --> 09:40.447
Oh, you know...

09:40.447 --> 09:41.881
I may have forgotten

09:41.881 --> 09:43.650
to put
the water-softening pellets

09:43.650 --> 09:44.751
in the tank.

09:44.751 --> 09:46.019
And now that I think
about it,

09:46.019 --> 09:48.254
I may have
accidentally replaced them

09:48.254 --> 09:51.124
with sodium hydroxide.

09:51.124 --> 09:53.760
If your eyes
weren't swollen shut,

09:53.760 --> 09:55.495
you'd be terrified
of the look on my face

09:55.495 --> 09:56.629
right now.

09:56.629 --> 09:57.764
Well,
I guess we're even, then.

09:57.764 --> 09:59.199
We are not even!

09:59.199 --> 10:00.600
You know what?

10:00.600 --> 10:01.868
You're right!

10:01.868 --> 10:03.436
You brought Dander
into this house,

10:03.436 --> 10:06.506
and in doing so,
you affected my health.

10:06.506 --> 10:08.374
I am having trouble
breathing.

10:08.374 --> 10:09.742
As am I!

10:09.742 --> 10:13.847
This tiny cashmere sweater
is compressing my lungs.

10:15.114 --> 10:17.717
I, uh, heard things
had gotten ugly

10:17.717 --> 10:19.285
between the two of you.

10:20.820 --> 10:22.422
Quite ugly.

10:22.422 --> 10:23.823
Okay, Dad...

10:23.823 --> 10:25.658
I brought you something else
to argue about.

10:25.658 --> 10:27.393
Milo has asked
to move in with me.

10:27.393 --> 10:28.895
What?
Yeah.

10:28.895 --> 10:30.430
I told him
if I was ever gonna shelter

10:30.430 --> 10:33.299
any one of your three kids,
it would be Mason.

10:33.299 --> 10:35.134
But that didn't seem
to stop him

10:35.134 --> 10:37.437
from having his mail
forwarded to my address.

10:37.437 --> 10:38.838
He doesn't get mail.
He's 8.

10:38.838 --> 10:41.908
It's an application
to Wisley.

10:41.908 --> 10:44.777
It's this school
for gifted kids

10:44.777 --> 10:46.346
where his friend Ajay
goes.

10:46.346 --> 10:48.515
The only way Milo's getting
into that school

10:48.515 --> 10:49.816
is through
the service entrance.

10:49.816 --> 10:51.784
I can't believe
he wants to move out.

10:51.784 --> 10:52.986
Listen.

10:52.986 --> 10:55.655
Could you two please declare
a truce?

10:55.655 --> 10:57.457
Before there's
a house-wide mutiny?

10:57.457 --> 10:59.726
♪♪

11:04.130 --> 11:06.399
How many changes of underwear
do I need?

11:06.399 --> 11:08.167
For life?

11:08.167 --> 11:09.769
Three?

11:09.769 --> 11:12.572
Sweetie, we don't want you
to move out.

11:12.572 --> 11:14.440
We would all be so sad.

11:14.440 --> 11:17.610
I mean, just think about how sad
and lonely Mason would be.

11:17.610 --> 11:18.845
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

11:18.845 --> 11:20.747
"All these laces,
and you still trippin'."

11:20.747 --> 11:21.848
[ Sighs ]

11:21.848 --> 11:23.216
He wouldn't even notice!

11:23.216 --> 11:25.318
He hasn't even noticed
that your hair

11:25.318 --> 11:27.887
looks like it got caught
in the garbage disposal.

11:27.887 --> 11:30.557
And that that Dad's face
looks like an STD.

11:30.557 --> 11:31.758
Face it.

11:31.758 --> 11:33.560
This family
has grown apart.

11:33.560 --> 11:35.428
We just want
different things.

11:35.428 --> 11:37.964
And what I want
is to live with my grandpa

11:37.964 --> 11:40.066
and to go to the school
for gifted kids.

11:40.066 --> 11:42.168
Yeah, well, neither of those
things are gonna happen, bud.

11:42.168 --> 11:44.604
Because we just can't
let you go.

11:44.604 --> 11:46.239
We love you too much.

11:46.239 --> 11:48.308
Besides, you don't really want
to live with Grandpa.

11:48.308 --> 11:50.443
The only thing he knows
how to make is tuna.

11:50.443 --> 11:51.444
He likes tuna.

11:51.444 --> 11:53.079
Mind your business.

11:53.079 --> 11:55.014
Sweetie, I know
that your daddy and I

11:55.014 --> 11:56.983
have been bickering a lot
lately --

11:56.983 --> 11:58.351
Well, I wouldn't call it
bickering --

11:58.351 --> 11:59.352
Quarreling.

11:59.352 --> 12:00.453
More like quibbling --

12:00.453 --> 12:02.121
They can't even agree
on what word to use

12:02.121 --> 12:03.556
to describe
their fighting.

12:03.556 --> 12:05.425
But that's over now.

12:05.425 --> 12:06.693
We've buried the hatchet.

12:06.693 --> 12:08.161
We did?
Yes.

12:08.161 --> 12:10.029
From now on, Mommy and Daddy
are gonna play nice,

12:10.029 --> 12:12.865
and everything's gonna go
back to normal, okay?

12:12.865 --> 12:14.667
What about
the smart kids' school?

12:14.667 --> 12:18.304
Well, I guess if you really
want to go to Wisley...

12:18.304 --> 12:19.872
Lena.
...we'll do what we can

12:19.872 --> 12:21.074
to help you try and get in.

12:21.074 --> 12:22.909
Deal?
Deal.

12:22.909 --> 12:24.978
♪♪

12:24.978 --> 12:26.913
Let's start by taking
my portrait.

12:26.913 --> 12:28.481
Do I look gifted
in this?

12:28.481 --> 12:29.649
Mae: Whoa!

12:29.649 --> 12:30.883
Dad's face looks like
an STD.

12:30.883 --> 12:32.652
And, Mom,
your hair is --

12:32.652 --> 12:34.454
Mae, take your brother
downstairs

12:34.454 --> 12:36.923
and get him some gifted photos
in front of the hearth.

12:36.923 --> 12:38.791
I'm sorry,
so we're all gonna pretend

12:38.791 --> 12:41.027
that Milo
is your gifted child?

12:41.027 --> 12:44.430
I mean...people.
Come on.

12:44.430 --> 12:47.033
Okay, Mae, you can be gifted
without being cocky.

12:47.033 --> 12:49.102
How would you know?

12:49.102 --> 12:50.370
Mm.
[ Exhales sharply ]

12:50.370 --> 12:53.339
Let me just grab
my writing feather.

12:53.339 --> 12:55.041
[ Sighs ]

12:55.041 --> 12:57.410
It's called a quill.

12:59.045 --> 13:00.246
Mason, your father and I

13:00.246 --> 13:02.348
need to have a chat
in private.

13:02.348 --> 13:03.750
This is my room!

13:03.750 --> 13:05.051
Fine.

13:05.051 --> 13:07.053
I know what you're gonna say
and I agree.

13:07.053 --> 13:08.454
You don't know
what I'm gonna say.

13:08.454 --> 13:10.590
"We can't let him do this,
blah, blah, blah."

13:10.590 --> 13:11.924
And you're right!

13:11.924 --> 13:13.526
He'll be crushed
when he doesn't get in,

13:13.526 --> 13:15.361
and he's just too young to face
that kind of rejection.

13:15.361 --> 13:17.764
That's not
what I was gonna say.

13:17.764 --> 13:19.065
I think
we should let him try.

13:19.065 --> 13:20.033
What's the worst
that could happen?

13:20.033 --> 13:21.367
What, he fails?

13:21.367 --> 13:22.869
It's good practice
for the rest of his life.

13:22.869 --> 13:24.570
These kids are gonna fail
constantly.

13:24.570 --> 13:26.806
But --
They don't know how
to deal with loss.

13:26.806 --> 13:28.074
Look at Mason.

13:28.074 --> 13:29.809
I mean, how long ago
did Hazel dump him?

13:29.809 --> 13:31.210
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

13:31.210 --> 13:32.812
"All this repellant,
and you still buggin'."

13:32.812 --> 13:34.947
Okay, that is not
the same thing.

13:34.947 --> 13:37.350
We both know
Milo doesn't have a shot.

13:37.350 --> 13:39.619
I mean, this school is
impossible to get into.

13:39.619 --> 13:41.220
He would need tutoring,

13:41.220 --> 13:42.689
And even then,
he probably still
wouldn't get in.

13:42.689 --> 13:44.290
Is Milo that dumb?

13:44.290 --> 13:45.692
Yes.
Yes.

13:45.692 --> 13:46.993
No.
No.

13:46.993 --> 13:50.229
Just academically,
it would be a stretch.

13:50.229 --> 13:52.031
And I am not interested

13:52.031 --> 13:53.666
in crushing
our 8-year-old's spirit.

13:53.666 --> 13:54.801
Well, then
why did you tell him

13:54.801 --> 13:56.202
you were gonna help him
get in, hmm?

13:56.202 --> 13:57.503
What is it with you,
Lena?

13:57.503 --> 13:59.372
What, you just tell people
what they wanna hear

13:59.372 --> 14:00.740
even if you don't
mean it?

14:00.740 --> 14:02.041
Did you mean it
when you said

14:02.041 --> 14:03.810
Hazel and I
still might have a chance?

14:03.810 --> 14:04.944
Sure I did.

14:04.944 --> 14:06.312
Get out.

14:06.312 --> 14:07.313
Hey.

14:07.313 --> 14:08.581
Please?

14:08.581 --> 14:12.318
♪♪

14:12.318 --> 14:13.352
Hurry up.

14:13.352 --> 14:14.954
You just missed me
looking gifted!

14:14.954 --> 14:16.856
I find that
hard to believe.

14:18.624 --> 14:21.327
Is this...too parse?

14:21.327 --> 14:22.428
Sparse.

14:22.428 --> 14:23.796
♪♪

14:23.796 --> 14:25.565
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

14:25.565 --> 14:27.633
♪♪

14:27.633 --> 14:29.435
Did you get it?

14:29.435 --> 14:30.470
Get what?

14:30.470 --> 14:32.238
♪♪

14:32.238 --> 14:34.440
♪ Yeah, you got this ♪

14:34.440 --> 14:36.008
♪ La-la, la-la ♪

14:36.008 --> 14:39.245
♪ La-la, la-la, la ♪

14:39.245 --> 14:42.148
We can't agree on anything
anymore --

14:42.148 --> 14:44.584
including how to parent
the kids.

14:44.584 --> 14:46.252
Milo wants to move out.

14:46.252 --> 14:48.154
Mason is clingy
and desperate.

14:48.154 --> 14:50.223
And Mae --
Mae. [ Chuckles ]

14:50.223 --> 14:51.758
Mae is your Maya.

14:51.758 --> 14:54.026
Dad.
I'm just saying.

14:54.026 --> 14:56.662
She's going to
require more.

14:56.662 --> 14:58.431
And she'll never marry.

14:58.431 --> 15:01.734
But there is still a joy
to be had from her.

15:01.734 --> 15:03.302
Geez, Dad.

15:03.302 --> 15:06.439
My whole point is that
the kids are gonna be fine.

15:06.439 --> 15:09.041
Right now, you're the one
I'm worried about.

15:09.041 --> 15:11.644
'Cause if you fall apart,
so does everything else.

15:11.644 --> 15:13.579
I'm not falling apart --

15:13.579 --> 15:17.016
Then why are you still wearing
that ridiculous sweater?

15:17.016 --> 15:19.552
All of this
is Martin's fault.

15:19.552 --> 15:21.187
He is provoking me,

15:21.187 --> 15:23.322
all because I don't want
to sell the house.

15:23.322 --> 15:25.057
You don't want
to get back together.

15:25.057 --> 15:27.660
But you don't want
to be apart.

15:27.660 --> 15:28.761
What do you want?

15:28.761 --> 15:30.196
I want things
to be like they were

15:30.196 --> 15:31.764
before we slept together.

15:32.598 --> 15:36.202
Well, I have no idea
if that's even possible.

15:36.202 --> 15:38.604
But if you want
a fighting chance...

15:40.306 --> 15:41.941
We have to stop fighting.

15:41.941 --> 15:46.012
♪♪

15:46.012 --> 15:47.346
All right.

15:47.346 --> 15:50.416
♪♪

15:55.154 --> 16:01.060
♪ Weightlessness, no gravity ♪

16:02.495 --> 16:06.933
♪ Were we somewhere
in between? ♪

16:06.933 --> 16:09.035
[ Scoffs ]
What are you doing here?

16:09.035 --> 16:11.237
Martin, I don't want
to fight with you.

16:11.237 --> 16:12.538
I mean,
we've made it this far

16:12.538 --> 16:14.273
without turning our house
into a war zone.

16:14.273 --> 16:16.209
Can't we just
hold our fire?

16:16.209 --> 16:18.244
♪ Ooh, ooh-ooh, ooh ♪

16:18.244 --> 16:20.112
If you want to hire
Vlad the contractor,

16:20.112 --> 16:21.881
we'll hire
Vlad the contractor.

16:21.881 --> 16:23.182
Is this another example

16:23.182 --> 16:25.518
of you just telling me
what I want to hear?

16:25.518 --> 16:27.119
I'll call the guy
and apologize.

16:27.119 --> 16:29.188
He can start Monday.

16:29.188 --> 16:31.591
And I won't wear
my glasses.

16:31.591 --> 16:33.259
So you're agreeing
to sell the house?

16:33.259 --> 16:35.561
No, I'm agreeing
to fix the house.

16:35.561 --> 16:38.631
The rest we'll figure out
when we get there.

16:40.299 --> 16:42.268
I can live with that.
Well, you don't have to.

16:42.268 --> 16:44.937
That's what the garage is for,
right?

16:44.937 --> 16:46.739
[ Chuckles ] Right.

16:46.739 --> 16:48.241
♪♪

16:48.241 --> 16:50.676
♪ I'm a ghost to you,
you're a ghost to me ♪

16:50.676 --> 16:52.345
♪ A birds-eye view
of San Luis ♪

16:52.345 --> 16:54.881
And, you know,
I'm not trying to be dishonest

16:54.881 --> 16:56.415
about my feelings.

16:56.415 --> 17:00.152
I just like to try
and cushion the blow.

17:00.152 --> 17:02.688
♪♪

17:02.688 --> 17:06.559
I don't like to see
our kids get hurt.

17:06.559 --> 17:09.095
I don't like to see
you get hurt either.

17:09.095 --> 17:10.563
♪♪

17:10.563 --> 17:13.199
Yeah, well,
sometimes people get hurt.

17:13.199 --> 17:16.502
Sometimes they need
to get hurt.

17:16.502 --> 17:21.007
And it's not always your job
to be the cushion, right?

17:21.007 --> 17:22.875
Right.

17:22.875 --> 17:24.644
The good news is,

17:24.644 --> 17:26.412
we may not have
to cushion anything.

17:26.412 --> 17:28.180
I mean,
what if we're wrong?

17:28.180 --> 17:29.515
What if Milo's
the kind of smart

17:29.515 --> 17:32.718
that normal people like us
just can't detect?

17:32.718 --> 17:33.886
Yeah.

17:33.886 --> 17:35.755
I mean, Einstein's parents
probably didn't know

17:35.755 --> 17:37.490
what they had on
their hands either.
Mm-hmm, mm-hmm.

17:37.490 --> 17:39.225
You know, weird-looking kid
with crazy hair.

17:39.225 --> 17:40.626
Who knew?
Yeah.

17:40.626 --> 17:42.628
Maybe we're doing
all this worrying for nothing.

17:42.628 --> 17:43.796
Yeah.

17:43.796 --> 17:47.833
♪♪

17:47.833 --> 17:49.769
Lena: What is he wearing?

17:49.769 --> 17:51.938
Martin: What is he doing?

17:51.938 --> 17:53.706
Well, he has a system.

17:53.706 --> 17:56.208
It's just outside the box.

17:56.208 --> 17:58.477
I think they want
inside the box.

17:58.477 --> 17:59.812
♪♪

18:02.715 --> 18:04.216
Hey! How did it go?

18:04.216 --> 18:05.451
I think I did amazing.

18:05.451 --> 18:07.320
Extremely excellent,
I should say.

18:07.320 --> 18:09.288
Good for you.
We love your confidence.

18:09.288 --> 18:11.223
Hey, look. It's Ajay.

18:11.223 --> 18:13.225
Ajay! Over here.

18:13.225 --> 18:14.493
Hello, Milo.

18:14.493 --> 18:16.395
Martin, Lena,
you're both looking well.

18:16.395 --> 18:17.496
Why, thank you, Ajay.
Oh. Thank you.

18:17.496 --> 18:18.864
Milo, would you like me

18:18.864 --> 18:20.466
to take you
on a tour of the school

18:20.466 --> 18:22.001
while your parents await word
from our dean?

18:22.001 --> 18:23.836
Is there a bathroom
I could tour?

18:23.836 --> 18:25.037
I need to go number two,

18:25.037 --> 18:26.839
or as they say
in Roman numerals,

18:26.839 --> 18:28.140
line line.

18:28.140 --> 18:29.942
Did you teach him that?
No.

18:29.942 --> 18:31.143
That's amazing.

18:31.143 --> 18:36.983
♪♪

18:36.983 --> 18:38.184
He might still get in.

18:38.184 --> 18:40.720
Yeah, it's a no.

18:40.720 --> 18:42.722
I hate this school.

18:42.722 --> 18:44.056
Me, too.

18:44.056 --> 18:51.263
♪♪

18:51.263 --> 18:52.264
How'd it go?

18:52.264 --> 18:54.000
-Well...
-Well...

18:54.000 --> 18:55.568
Really well.

18:56.402 --> 18:58.504
-You got in?
-They didn't say I didn't.

19:00.406 --> 19:04.543
Okay, buddy.
Here's the deal.

19:04.543 --> 19:06.145
They did say
you didn't.

19:06.145 --> 19:07.747
That's what I said.

19:07.747 --> 19:09.348
No. No, no, no.
I think --

19:09.348 --> 19:11.884
I think you're confusing "did"
and "didn't."

19:11.884 --> 19:13.319
They said you didn't.

19:13.319 --> 19:15.154
But they didn't say
I did.

19:15.154 --> 19:16.188
That's correct.

19:16.188 --> 19:19.892
Yes.
Got another one right.

19:19.892 --> 19:22.161
Milo, sweetie.

19:22.161 --> 19:23.896
They don't want you.

19:23.896 --> 19:25.998
What?

19:25.998 --> 19:27.433
Did they see
my pictures?

19:27.433 --> 19:28.801
They did, buddy.

19:28.801 --> 19:30.669
They saw me
measuring a banana?

19:30.669 --> 19:33.172
Yeah.
Even that didn't do it.

19:33.172 --> 19:34.907
Oh.

19:34.907 --> 19:36.842
I guess I'm not gifted.

19:36.842 --> 19:40.312
♪♪

19:40.312 --> 19:41.847
Well, hold on.

19:41.847 --> 19:44.316
Hold on.
You didn't let me finish.

19:44.316 --> 19:45.751
You didn't get into Wisley,

19:45.751 --> 19:48.287
because that school
is on Earth.

19:50.056 --> 19:52.491
Your test scores showed

19:52.491 --> 19:53.993
that you are
out of this world,

19:53.993 --> 19:58.230
which is why you're getting
a full scholarship...

19:58.230 --> 19:59.198
to space school!

19:59.198 --> 20:01.400
Shut your beautiful mouth!

20:01.400 --> 20:03.235
I will not!

20:03.235 --> 20:04.503
Because it's true,
baby!

20:04.503 --> 20:05.771
You're going to space.

20:05.771 --> 20:06.839
Hear that, Mae?

20:06.839 --> 20:09.208
I'm gonna be blasting off!
In your face!

20:09.208 --> 20:10.242
When do I leave?

20:10.242 --> 20:11.610
2061.

20:11.610 --> 20:13.612
Guess I'd better pack.

20:14.346 --> 20:15.347
He really is that dumb.

20:15.347 --> 20:16.482
[ Exhales slowly ]

20:16.482 --> 20:18.484
Yeah.
Oh, yeah.

20:23.489 --> 20:27.726
So, I guess
you changed your mind

20:27.726 --> 20:31.430
about the kids
needing rejection?

20:31.430 --> 20:33.632
Yeah, well, I-I said
it wasn't your job

20:33.632 --> 20:35.501
to always be
the cushion.

20:35.501 --> 20:38.671
So today was my day.

20:38.671 --> 20:39.505
Hmm.

20:39.505 --> 20:42.007
Alternating cushions.

20:42.007 --> 20:43.075
Like a dirty couch.

20:43.075 --> 20:44.043
I like that.

20:44.043 --> 20:45.211
[ Chuckles ]

20:45.211 --> 20:47.113
You like that?

20:47.113 --> 20:49.315
No, I don't like that.

20:49.315 --> 20:52.284
But I prefer not fighting.

20:52.284 --> 20:54.854
Yeah. Me, too.

20:54.854 --> 20:56.789
♪♪

20:56.789 --> 21:00.826
And, listen, I-I'm sorry
I made your throat close up.

21:00.826 --> 21:02.595
Yeah, um...

21:02.595 --> 21:05.531
I'm sorry about making
your hair fall out.

21:05.531 --> 21:07.733
My hair
didn't fall out.

21:07.733 --> 21:08.901
Yeah.

21:10.870 --> 21:12.138
It will.

21:12.138 --> 21:14.206
♪♪

21:14.206 --> 21:15.674
[ Dog whines ]

21:15.674 --> 21:17.109
♪♪

21:17.109 --> 21:19.545
[ Door opens ]

21:19.545 --> 21:21.747
[ Door closes ]
